    "explanation": "<p>The correct answer is <strong>Bismillah Khan</strong>.</p>\n<p><p><strong>Bismillah Khan</strong> became the first Indian to be invited to perform at the prestigious Lincoln Centre Hall in the United States of America.</p></p>\n<p><p>He also participated in the World Exposition in Montreal, the Cannes Art Festival, and the Osaka Trade Fair.</p></p>\n<p><p>His international fame led to an auditorium in Tehran being named after him — Tahar Mosiquee Ustaad Bismillah Khan.</p></p>\n<p><p>He was honored with numerous national awards, including the Padma Shri, the Padma Bhushan, and the Padma Vibhushan.</p></p>\n<p><p>In 2001, Ustad Bismillah Khan was awarded India’s highest civilian award, the Bharat Ratna.</p></p>",
